ki/Ring_species\" rel=\"nofollow\">ring species<\/a> - the boundaries of species are sometimes really hard to define."},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/9905bf9a7b8d5a587c1bdff07ef2e801?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":239,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/239/ilmari-karonen","reputation":2067,"display_name":"Ilmari Karonen"},"score":1,"post_id":1605,"edited":false,"creation_date":1333730821,"comment_id":2199,"body":"As an aside, I&#39;m fairly sure that a Miniature Pinscher <i>can<\/i> mate with a Great Dane and produce viable offspring. While I haven&#39;t seen that particular crossbreed myself, a friend of mine used to have a dog who was half Siberian Husky and half Papillon. (And before you ask, yes, the Husky was the mother. The moral of the story being either &quot;love conquers all&quot; or &quot;make sure to keep female dogs in heat away from <i>all<\/i> males if you don&#39;t want puppies&quot;, depending on how you look at it.)"},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/9905bf9a7b8d5a587c1bdff07ef2e801?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":239,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/239/ilmari-karonen","reputation":2067,"display_name":"Ilmari Karonen"},"score":0,"post_id":1605,"edited":false,"creation_date":1333730865,"comment_id":2200,"body":"Ps. See also this question on Yahoo! Answers: <a href=\"http://answers.yahoo.com/question/index?qid=20070211165254AAHBQ6w\" rel=\"nofollow\">Can you crossbreed a Chihuahua with a Great Dane?<\/a>"},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/OxfyD.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":3059,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/3059/dd3","reputation":2303,"display_name":"dd3","accept_rate":95},"score":0,"post_id":1605,"edited":false,"creation_date":1363722312,"comment_id":9457,"body":"As many have pointed out, Canis familiaris is one species.  A more interesting consideration mig