Smith-Unna","accept_rate":90},"score":0,"post_id":3487,"edited":false,"creation_date":1347309636,"comment_id":5306,"body":"It&#39;s not the chance of both eggs being excluded that Dawkins talks about, he talks about the chance of having an egg excluded. It&#39;s still true that it would be worth cheating for the first few birds. The wider point about the trait not being an ESS might be true, but his specific explanation is not. In your specific example, if there are 105 eggs and 5 are excluded, each egg has a ~5% (more precisely, 4.76%), not ~1%, chance of being excluded. In any case, your question was interesting so I&#39;m writing a model of the Guillemot situation. I&#39;ll report back when done :)"}],"answers":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/889548c1e8387b3d381853dee5212cfd?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":3632,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/3632/shigeta","reputation":22684,"display_name":"shigeta","accept_rate":86},"score":-1,"is_accepted":false,"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/f3d2c01f6f55bb34530fcbae9a39d285?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":185,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/185/dvk","reputation":1488,"display_name":"DVK","accept_rate":50},"score":0,"post_id":3488,"edited":false,"creation_date":1347204802,"comment_id":5268,"body":"My question was mostly aimed at game theoretical ones"},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/f3d2c01f6f55bb34530fcbae9a39d285?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":185,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/185/dvk","reputation":1488,"display_name":"DVK","accept_rate":50},"score":0,"post_id":3488,"edited":false,"creation_date":1347204952,"comment_id":5269,"body":"Please see updates to the question. I&#39;m not asking how the models are tested. I&#39;m asking what language (if a standard one exists) is used to communicate the model para