ction favour birds with flesh at all if it hinders their flight.<\/p>\n\n<p>We started first with single-cell and micro-organisms flourishing the ponds and then they evolved into massive dinosaurs. It therefore seems, there are some unique reasons for growing to such a large size.<\/p>\n\n<p>However, I thought it's counter intuitive because the large body slows down locomotion, requires lots of food and energy upkeep, is a big flesh target for predators, makes hiding ineffective.<\/p>\n\n<p>Although it is obvious that the flesh protects the internal organs, but it seems like a chicken and egg problem because without a massive body, perhaps then there is no need for the internal organs.<\/p>\n\n<p>On a different perspective, perhaps those animals that evolved without flesh are called plants.<\/p>\n\n<p>That sums up my naive train of thoughts.<\/p>\n\n<p>So, any expert can shed some light?<\/p>\n","question_id":7242,"tags":["evolution","natural-selection"],"score":4,"accepted_answer_id":7244,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":true,"view_count":306,"up_vote_count":4},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/718431537bd663864194f6f3462f3563?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":3100,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/3100/tull-pung","reputation":6,"display_name":"Tull Pung"},"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/VmtoK.png?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":1320,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/1320/alan-boyd","reputation":17240,"display_name":"Alan Boyd"},"score":0,"post_id":7228,"edited":false,"creation_date":1361034145,"comment_id":8945,"body":"The preparation of a soluble antigen for injection often includes treatment with an adjuvant which usually creates aggregates of some sort. It is my understanding that particulate antigenic material is preferable because it elicits a better immune response."},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/718431537b